# .dockerignore applied to the cookbooks repo root when building from
# deploy/railway/Dockerfile.
#
# Goal: keep the runtime image small by excluding files that aren't
# needed by the server or the init script.

.git
.gitignore
LICENSE

# Repo-wide documentation
docs/
**/README.md
**/CLAUDE.md

# Per-cookbook prose seed (`seed.jsonl` is the data, `seed.md` is the
# write-up; only the former is loaded at deploy time)
**/seed.md

# Local dev credentials — never bake into an image
**/.env.omni
**/.env.omni.example

# Agent skill packaging — installed via `npx skills`, not deploy artifact
skills/

# Build / editor noise
**/.DS_Store
**/.idea
**/.vscode
